            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">Who is Front Porch Church for?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                Front Porch Church is for everyone. No matter your age, background, ability, belief, or life experience. You are welcome here.
                We believe the church is a place of belonging before anything else.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">Is there an age range?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                All ages are welcome at Front Porch Church. Children, teens, adults, and older adults are an important part of our community,
                and we value learning and worshiping together across generations.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">Is Front Porch Church accessible for people with disabilities?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                Yes. Front Porch Church is an all-abilities community. People with disabilities are not just welcomed, they participate, serve,
                and lead alongside others in the life of the church. If there is something specific you’d like us to know or a way we can better
                support you or your family, please contact us. We’re always learning and happy to have that conversation.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">What if my child or I need to move, make noise, or take breaks?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                That’s okay here. Front Porch Church values interaction over perfection. Movement, sounds, questions, and breaks are part of how
                people engage, and you are welcome to participate in the ways that work best for you.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">What kind of church is Front Porch?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                Front Porch Church is a Christian community rooted in the life and teachings of Jesus. We are not tied to a specific denomination
                and seek to be a welcoming place for people from a variety of church backgrounds or none at all.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">What do you believe?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                We center our faith on Jesus Christ and seek to follow Him in love, hospitality, justice, and humility. We believe faith is something
                that grows through worship, Scripture, prayer, and shared life together, and we welcome questions along the way.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">Do I need to believe a certain way to attend?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                No. You do not need to have everything figured out to belong here. Front Porch Church is a place for curiosity, exploration, and growth.
                Wherever you are on your faith journey, you are welcome.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">What should I wear?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
