              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">What happens during a typical service?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
                Our gatherings follow a simple, welcoming rhythm. We begin with a brief host moment that walks through the flow of the service so everyone
                knows what to expect. Early on, you’ll experience Otis &amp; Friends, a lighthearted moment that highlights some of our community’s furry friends
                and reminds us of the joy of shared life. From there, we spend time in worship through music, followed by a message from our teaching team.
                We also share announcements and receive an offering as part of our life together. We close each service by holding hands and singing a benediction
                that is a reminder that we go out connected and sent into the week ahead.
              </span>
            </button>

            <button class="faqItem" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faqQ">How can I learn more or ask additional questions?</span>
              <span class="faqIcon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              <span class="faqA">
